<l>oṉṟumuta lāka veṭṭa ṉiṟuti</l>
<l>yellā veṇṇum pattaṉ muṉvariṟ</l>
<l>kuṟṟiya lukara meyyoṭuṅ keṭumē</l>
<l>muṟṟa viṉvarūu miraṇṭalaṅ kaṭaiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Learned men say that, to denote the angular directions, the</l>
<l>consonant and the final [<foreign xml:lang="ta">-u</foreign>] must disappear ; and when combining</l>
<l>with <foreign xml:lang="ta">teṟku,</foreign> the consonant [<foreign xml:lang="ta">ṟ</foreign>] is also changed to the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṉ.</foreign></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
